 What Where Find Jobs Advanced Job Search Vice President, Digital Quality Resilience 6 reviews La Jolla, CA Resilience 6 reviews Read what people are saying about working here. Job details Job Type Full-time Full Job Description Ready to join a team dedicated to quality excellence, innovation and the advance of complex medicine manufacturing supporting patients worldwide? Are you an architect at heart and love designing and developing systems and processes from the ground up? We just started an incredible journey and are looking for passionate leaders to join us on this important mission.
 This role is accountable for the development, implementation and lifecycle management of the Digital Quality and Compliance program. The Vice President, Digital Quality is a key leadership role and reports to the Chief Quality Officer. The position will be located at one of our Resilience network offices.
 Responsibilities
 Accountable for the development and implementation of the global digital compliance strategy
 Provides quality oversight of the digital roadmap development, implementation and operations
 Accountable for the development and lifecycle management of policies and standards in support of deployment and maintenance of computerized systems
 Collaborates with Quality peers and stakeholders and ensures a compliant design and execution of the Quality Management System to meet digital needs
 Partners with key stakeholders and provides strategic and compliance guidance during the selection and implementation of technology platforms (robotics, automation, business analytics, complex manufacturing and testing instrumentation, software testing and automation tool selection, artificial intelligence and machine learning tools, etc.)
 Oversees the development of data integrity standards to assure the completeness, consistency and accuracy of GMP data, in alignment with regulatory requirements. Provides guidance to Resilience sites for remediation of deficiencies, as required.
 Oversees the development of master validation plans and provides quality guidance and oversight of the validation of computerized system program, including selection and management of validation e-tools
 Oversees the computerized system change management program
 Supports inspection readiness plans and interacts with regulatory agencies during inspections on computerized systems and data integrity related matters
 Develops and manages departmental goals and corresponding budget in alignment with corporate vision and goals
 Recruits talent and builds a high performance team; mentors and coaches personnel
 Qualifications
 Comprehensive knowledge of global GMP regulatory requirements
 Hands on experience in developing and managing an effective Quality Management System in support of digital needs
 Hands-on experience with managing IT compliance and providing quality oversight of computerized systems validation
 Demonstrated experience with implementing systems and processes to assure data integrity
 Excellent oral and written communication skills with strong technical writing experience required
 Ability to synthesize data and summarize outcomes to provide recommendations on a compliant path forward
 Demonstrated ability to set goals, perform long-term project planning, team building, budgeting and operational excellence
 Demonstrated ability to successfully execute responsibilities in a fast-pace environment, collaborating across multiple sites and stakeholders
 Ability to travel
 Preferred Experience
 Bachelorâ€™s degree or higher in IT, Life Sciences, Chemistry, Engineering, or related field
